  "texts": [
    "But new developments in generative AI offer the tantalizing prospect of a new kind of recommender system, one that could make us better, rather than worse, moral agents.",
    "This isn't meant as a critique of Watzl, however, since he may not share our purposes.",
    "We develop our framework specifically to guide moral assessment of attention allocation and ultimately to ground our sociotechnical critique of algorithmic recommendation.",
    "We want to stress that as long as you save the child, you do the right thing, on our view.",
    "Our point is just that, in doing the right thing, you can still exhibit better or worse moral agency through your attention allocation."
  ],
